UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 22
1 AN ACT relating to court costs.
2 Be it enacted by the General Assembly of the Commonwealth of Kentucky:
3 Section 1. KRS 454.460 is amended to read as follows:
4 As used in KRS 454.460 to 454.478:
5 (1) "Cause of action" does not include:
6 (a) A procedural action taken or motion made in an action that does not amend or
7 add a claim for legal, equitable, or declaratory relief; or
8 (b) Post-judgment enforcement actions;
9 (2) "Filed in bad faith":
10 (a) Means presenting to the court a pleading, written motion, or other paper for
11 any improper purpose, such as to harass, cause unnecessary delay, or
12 needlessly increase the cost of litigation; and
13 (b) Does not include:
14 1. Knowledge, information, and belief, formed after a reasonable inquiry
15 that the claim, defense, or other legal contention is well grounded in
16 fact and warranted by existing law; or
17 2. A good-faith argument for the extension, modification, or reversal of
18 existing law;
19 (3) "Goods or services" does not include the creation, dissemination, exhibition, or
20 advertisement or similar promotion of a dramatic, literary, musical, political,
21 journalistic, or artistic work;
22 (4)[(3)] "Governmental unit" means a public corporation, government, or government
23 subdivision, agency, or instrumentality;
24 (5)[(4)] "Matter of public concern" means a statement or activity regarding:
25 (a) A public official, public figure, or other person who has drawn substantial
26 public attention due to the person's official acts, fame, notoriety, or celebrity;
27 (b) A matter of political, social, or other interest to the community; or
Page 1 of 2
