UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 22
1 (c) A subject of concern to the public; and
2 (6)[(5)] "Person" means an individual, estate, trust, partnership, business or nonprofit
3 entity, governmental unit, or other legal entity.
4 Section 2. KRS 454.478 is amended to read as follows:
5 On a motion under KRS 454.464, or the appeal of an order granting or denying a motion
6 under KRS 454.464, the court shall award court costs, reasonable attorney's fees, and
7 reasonable litigation expenses related to the motion:
8 (1) To the moving party if the moving party prevails on the motion and the court finds
9 that the responding party's complaint, crossclaim, counterclaim, third-party
10 claim, or other pleading that asserts a cause of action was filed in bad faith; or
11 (2) To the responding party if the responding party prevails on the motion and the court
12 finds that the moving party's motion was filed in bad faith[motion was brought
13 without good cause].
